Package: MSOmicsDesign
Title: Experiment design for MS-based omics study
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Kittinun", "Leetanaporn", , "kittinun.l@psu.ac.th", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7621-4510"))
Description: Provides tools for designing mass spectrometry-based omics
    experiments. Covers two main workflows: (1) sample plate design —
    inserting QC runs, block-randomising by experimental covariates,
    distributing samples across multi-well plates, visualising plate layouts,
    and exporting position lists for Thermo Xcalibur sequence files; and
    (2) data-independent acquisition (DIA) window design — generating
    fixed-width, variable-width (density-weighted), and gas-phase
    fractionation (GPF) isolation window lists with optional edge
    optimisation for reduced chimeric spectra.
